│ happens because the `match` condition, which should have prevented this for `icmp`         │
│ instructions with different predicates, is flawed.\n\n### 3. Root Cause Analysis\n\nThe    │
│ root cause is a bug in the `llvm::detail::CmpPattern` matcher, which is used by            │
│ `m_SpecificCmp`. The `match` method of this pattern class is intended to check for a       │
│ specific predicate.\n\n```cpp\n// llvm/include/llvm/IR/PatternMatch.h\ntemplate <typename  │
│ Pred_t>\nstruct CmpPattern<Pred_t, true /* Specific */> {\n  // ...\n  bool match(CmpInst  │
